properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system moving through southern Saskatchewan continues to bring rainfall to parts of the province. The Meadow Lake region is likely to see a further 20 to 30 mm of rainfall today. The rain will ease by evening. There have been areas in the region that have seen significant rainfall over the previous few days. ### Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system in south central Saskatchewan continues to move northward and is spreading rain and thunderstorms into southwestern Saskatchewan this morning. Rainfall amounts will vary widely but most areas should see 20 to 30 mm. Thunderstorms could push local rainfall amounts above 50 mm. The rainfall is expected to shift northward today and gradually move out of the area. ### Heavy rainfall in combination with other weather factors, such as hail, wind and lightning will make outdoor activities unsafe. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant Rainfall for Northeastern BC This Weekend. A series of disturbances moving through northeastern BC will continue to give periods of moderate to heavy rainfall through Monday. Potential impacts for this event include rising rivers and destabilizing slopes. An already moist air mass will be enhanced by upslope flow, particularly on the east slopes of the Northern Rockies. The communities of Liard River, Muncho Lake, Toad River, Nelson Forks, Sikanni Chief and their surrounding higher terrain may see up to 50 to 80 mm of total rainfall. These areas have experienced moderate rainfall events over the past few weeks thus the ground is quite saturated in some places. Stay tuned to your local weather forecast and alerts: www.weather.gc.ca Flood Warnings and Advisories can be viewed at: http://bcrfc.env.gov.bc.ca/warnings/index.htm Road Conditions: https://drivebc.ca/ ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.

properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Rain, at times heavy, is expected. Widespread rain, at times heavy, will continue today over eastern Alberta and western Saskatchewan with total accumulations of 50-75 mm expected. Rainfall will begin to taper off over southern Alberta today while areas east and northeast of Edmonton can expect heavy rainfall to persist until early Monday morning. Rain will end late this evening in Buffalo Narrows, SK. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Rainfall warnings are issued when significant rainfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ABstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ABStorm.
